<HR size="1" color="#5d7790">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
The balance of smoking/non-smoking is (and always has been) a problem in the Gregson. WE are slowly and significantly improving things, until 2 years ago there was no no-smoking area at all, now 30% of our cafe/bar area is non-smoking and we discourage smoking at either of the bar/serving areas and in the raised family area during the day time. We have also recently made one of our two function rooms non-smoking, and in the cafe/bar we having just upgraded the smoke extraction system to almost double its capacity to remove smoke. Basically our view as centre managers is that, given sustained steady gentle pressure no-smoking will in due course become the dominant mode of existence in the Gregson and in the meantime we use technical improvements wherever possible to help all customers.
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#5d7790">
